y under your control.\nParker could have customers eating out of his hand.', '完全受（某人）支配;完全听命于（某人）\n帕克能让顾客对自己言听计从。'], ['PHRASE\nIf someone is bound hand and foot, both their hands and both their feet are tied together.', '连手带脚地，手脚一起地（捆绑）'], ["PHRASE\nIf you force someone's hand, you force them to act sooner than they want to, or to act in public when they would prefer to keep their actions secret.\nHe blamed the press for forcing his hand.", '迫使（某人）提前行动（或公开其所作所为）\n他指责新闻界迫使自己采取行动。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you have your hands full with something, you are very busy because of it.\nShe had her hands full with new arrivals.', '（为…）忙得不可开交;（因…）应接不暇\n她忙于应付新来的人。'], ['PHRASE\nIf someone gives you a free hand, they give you the freedom to use your own judgment and to do exactly as you wish.\nHe gave Stephanie a free hand in the decoration.', '自行决定权;自由行动权\n他放手让斯蒂芬妮全权负责装修一事。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you say that someone is making or losing money hand over fist, you mean that they are getting or losing a lot of money very quickly.', '迅速而大量地（赚钱或花钱）'], ['PHRASE\nIf you get your hands on something or lay your hands on something, you manage to find it or obtain it, usually after some difficulty.\nPatty began reading everything she could get her hands on.', '（通常指经过努力后）获得，得到\n帕蒂开始阅读她能找到的所有东西。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you work hand in glove with someone, you work very closely with them.\nThe UN inspectors work hand in glove with the Western intelligence agencies.', '（与某人）密切合作地\n联合国观察员和西方情报机构之间密切合作。'], ["PHRASE\nIf two people are hand in hand, they are holding each other's nearest hand, usually while they are walking or sitting together. People often do this to show their affection for each other.\nI saw them making their way, hand in hand, down the path.", '（常指为表示爱意而）手拉手的，携着手的\n我看到他们手拉手沿着小路往前走去。'], ['PHRASE\nIf two things go hand in hand, they are closely connected and cannot be considered separately from each other.\nFor us, research and teaching go hand in hand...\nHand in hand with the police inquiries the government has also announced a full investigation.', '（两件事）密切相关地，同时并进地\n对我们而言，研究和教学是齐头并进的。\n在警方调查的同时，政府也宣布要展开彻查。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you have a hand in something such as an event or activity, you are involved in it.\nHe thanked all who had a hand in his release.', '参加;参与\n他向所有帮助自己获得释放的人表示感谢。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you say that someone such as the ruler of a country treats people with a heavy hand, you are criticizing them because they are very strict and severe with them.\nHenry and Richard both ruled with a heavy hand.', '（统治者）用高压手段，严厉地\n亨利和理查都用高压手段实行统治。'], ["PHR-RECIP\nIf two people are holding hands, they are holding each other's nearest hand, usually while they are walking or sitting together. People often do this to show their affection for each other.\nShe approached a young couple holding hands on a bench.", '（常指为表示爱意而）手拉手，牵手\n她走近一对手拉手坐在长椅上的年轻情侣。'], ["PHRASE\nIf you ask someone to hold your hand at an event that you are worried about, you ask them to support you by being there with you.\nI don't need anyone to hold my hand.", '给…精神上的支持\n我不需要任何人的精神安慰。'], ['PHRASE\nIn a competition, if someone has games or matches in hand, they have more games or matches left to play than their opponent and therefore have the possibility of scoring more points.\nWales are three points behind Romania in the group but have a game in hand.', '（比赛）尚待进行\n威尔士队在小组中以3分之差落后于罗马尼亚队，但他们还有一场比赛没踢。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you have time or money in hand, you have more time or money than you need.', '（时间或金钱）宽余的\nHughes finished with 15 seconds in hand.\n休斯提前了15秒完成。'], ['PHRASE\nThe job or problem in hand is the job or problem that you are dealing with at the moment.\nThe business in hand was approaching some kind of climax.', '（工作或问题）办理中的，处理中的\n手头的生意似乎快到紧要关头了。'], ['PHRASE\nIf a situation is in hand, it is under control.\nThe Olympic organisers say that matters are well in hand.', '（局势）在控制下，在掌握中\n奥运会的组织方说各项事务都在掌控之中。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you do something to keep your hand in, you practise a skill or hobby occasionally in order to remain fairly good at it.\nHe still plays keyboards for a local band to keep his hand in.', '偶尔练习以保持熟练\n他仍在一个本地乐队里担任键盘手，以免技艺生疏。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you are on your hands and knees, your knees and feet and the palms of your hands are touching the ground.\nChris crawled on his hands and knees out onto the highway.', '趴着;四肢着地\n克里斯手脚并用爬上了公路。'], ["PHRASE\nIf you lend someone a hand, you help them.\nI'd be glad to lend a hand.", '向…伸出援手;给予…帮助\n我很乐意帮忙。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you tell someone to keep their hands off something or to take their hands off it, you are telling them in a rather aggressive way not to touch it or interfere with it.\nKeep your hands off my milk.', '（不客气的警告语）别碰…，别干涉…\n不准打我的牛奶的主意。'], ["PHRASE\nIf you do not know something off hand, you do not know it without having to ask someone else or look it up in a book.\nI can't think of any off hand.", '马上;立即;无需询问（或查证）\n我现在一个也想不出来。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you have a problem or responsibility on your hands, you have to deal with it. If it is off your hands, you no longer have to deal with it.\nThey now have yet another drug problem on their hands...\nShe would like the worry of dealing with her affairs taken off her hands.', '由…负责/不再由…负责\n他们现在又有个吸毒问题需要解决。\n她希望不再为处理自己的事务而烦恼。'], ['PHRASE\nIf someone or something is on hand, they are near and able to be used if they are needed.\nThe Bridal Department will have experts on hand to give you all the help and advice you need...\nThere was simply no cash on hand to meet the cost of food.', '在手头;在近处;现有\n婚礼用品部会有现成的专家为您提供所需的一切帮助和建议。\n手头实在没有现金可以购买食品。'], ["PHRASE\nYou use on the one hand to introduce the first of two contrasting points, facts, or ways of looking at something. It is always followed later by on the other hand or 'on the other'.\nOn the one hand, if the body doesn't have enough cholesterol, we would not be able to survive. On the other hand, if the body has too much cholesterol, the excess begins to line the arteries.", '一方面…（另一方面…）\n一方面，如果体内没有足够的胆固醇，我们就无法存活下去。另一方面，如果体内胆固醇过高，多余的胆固醇就会附着在动脉内壁上。'], ["PHRASE\nYou use on the other hand to introduce the second of two contrasting points, facts, or ways of looking at something.\nWell, all right, hospitals lose money. But, on the other hand, if people are healthy, don't think of it as losing money; think of it as saving lives.", '（从）另一方面（来说）（用于引出相对照的另一点）\n嗯，好吧，医院是赔钱。但从另一个角度看，如果人们都健健康康的，就不能认为是在赔钱，而应该想成是在救死扶伤。'], ['PHRASE\nIf a person or a situation gets out of hand, you are no longer able to control them.\nHis drinking had got out of hand.', '失去控制;不可收拾\n他酗酒的恶习已无法控制。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you dismiss or reject something out of hand, you do so immediately and do not consider believing or accepting it.\nI initially dismissed the idea out of hand.', '立即，不假思索地（屏弃、拒绝等）\n我起初不假思索地就否定了这个想法。'], ["PHRASE\nIf you play into someone's hands, you do something which they want you to do and which places you in their power.\nHe is playing into the hands of racists.", '因失算而让…占便宜;做对…有利的事\n他这样做正中种族主义分子的下怀。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you show your hand, you show how much power you have and the way you intend to act.\nHe has grown more serious about running for president, although he refuses to show his hand.', '摊牌;亮出底牌;表明自己的真实意图\n尽管他拒绝亮出自己的底牌，他对竞选总统一事却越来越认真了。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you take something or someone in hand, you take control or responsibility over them, especially in order to improve them.\nI hope that Parliament will soon take the NHS in hand...\nHe had thought her worth taking in hand.', '（尤指为有所改善）接手，照管，担任起对…的责任\n我希望议会能很快接管国民医疗保健系统。\n他曾经认为照管她是值得的。'], ["PHRASE\nIf someone throws up their hands, they express their anger, frustration, or disgust when a situation becomes so bad that they can no longer accept it.\nShe threw up her hands in despair...\nOr are they just going to throw up their hands and say you're asking too much?", '（因愤怒、绝望或厌恶而）骤然举起双手\n她绝望地举起双手表示放弃。\n或许他们只会愤怒地挥舞着双手说你的要求太过分了？'], ['PHRASE\nIf you say that your hands are tied, you mean that something is preventing you from acting in the way that you want to.\nPoliticians are always saying that they want to help us but their hands are tied...\nHer hands were tied by the way that the US constitution is structured.', '受到束缚;放不开手脚\n政客们总是说想帮助我们，但却身不由己。\n她为美国宪法的表述缚住了手脚。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you have something to hand or near to hand, you have it with you or near you, ready to use when needed.\nYou may want to keep this brochure safe, so you have it to hand whenever you may need it.', '在手边;在附近\n你应该保管好这份手册，这样随时想用都能马上在手边找到。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you try your hand at an activity, you attempt to do it, usually for the first time.', '（通常指初次）尝试，试身手\nAfter he left school, he tried his hand at a variety of jobs—bricklayer, cinema usher, coal man.\n离开学校后，他尝试过各种工作，如泥瓦匠、电影院引座员、运煤工。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you turn your hand to something such as a practical activity, you learn about it and do it for the first time.\n...a person who can turn his hand to anything.', '着手学做\n什么事都能学着做的人'], ['PHRASE\nIf you wash your hands of someone or something, you refuse to be involved with them any more or to take responsibility for them.\nHe seems to have washed his hands of the job.', '洗手不干;不再管;和…断绝关系\n那份工作他好像已经洗手不干了。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you win hands down, you win very easily.\nB\nVERB USES', '轻易取胜\n动词用法'], ['VERB\nIf you hand something to someone, you pass it to them.\nHe handed me a little rectangle of white paper...\nHe took a thick envelope from an inside pocket and handed it to me.', '递;交;给\n他递给我一张小小的长方形白纸片。\n他从内侧口袋里掏出一只厚信封递给我。'], ["PHRASE\nYou say things such as 'You have to hand it to her' or 'You've got to hand it to them' when you admire someone for their skills or achievements and you think they deserve a lot of praise.\nYou've got to hand it to Melissa, she certainly gets around.\nhand round", '你不得不佩服…\n你不得不佩服梅利莎，她到哪里都吃得开。\n相关词组\nhand around\xa0\xa0\xa0\nhand back\xa0\xa0\xa0\nhand down\xa0\xa0\xa0\nhand in\xa0\xa0\xa0\nhand on\xa0\xa0\xa0\nhand out\xa0\xa0\xa0\nhand over\xa0\xa0\xa0']]}]